citations:
    citation-affc-samwell-aemon-death:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Samwell III"
            text_from_source: "He was a great man. A maester of the Citadel, chained and sworn, and Sworn Brother of the Night's Watch, ever faithful."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Maester Aemon Targaryen (age 102) dies at sea aboard the Cinnamon Wind, south of Dorne, after the stormy passage from Braavos. Sam delivers the eulogy: 'He was Aemon Targaryen. And now his watch is ended.' Before dying, Aemon spoke of Daenerys as the fulfillment of the prince-that-was-promised prophecy — not Rhaegar or his son Aegon, but Daenerys, born amidst salt and smoke. He begged Sam to tell the archmaesters. Sam sold Aemon's books and possessions to pay for passage south. Aemon's Valyrian steel sword and chain were all that remained. Note: the existing citation-affc-samwell-iii covers the earlier Braavos chapter. This chapter may be labeled Samwell IV in the source text."
